Michigan is a state located in the Great Lakes region of the United States of America. It is situated in the northern central part of the country and is bordered by four of the five Great Lakes (Lake Superior, Lake Michigan, Lake Huron, and Lake Erie).

Michigan is divided into two peninsulas: the Upper Peninsula (UP) and the Lower Peninsula. The UP is located to the north of the Lower Peninsula and is separated from the rest of the state by the Straits of Mackinac, which connects Lake Michigan and Lake Huron. The Lower Peninsula is bordered by Indiana and Ohio to the south, Wisconsin to the west, and the Canadian province of Ontario to the east.

Michigan is the 11th largest state by area and the 10th most populous state in the U.S. Its largest city is Detroit, and its capital is Lansing.